===Verb===
{{en-verb|shears|shearing|'''[[sheared]]''' ''or'' '''[[shore]]'''|'''[[shorn]] '''or''' [[sheared]]'''}}

# To [[cut]], originally with a sword or other bladed weapon, now usually with [[shears]], or as if using shears.
#:*'''1819''': So trenchant was the Templar’s weapon, that it '''shore''' asunder, as it had been a willow twig, the tough and plaited handle of the mace, which the ill-fated Saxon reared to parry the blow, and, descending on his head, levelled him with the earth. — Walter Scott, ''Ivanhoe''
# To [[remove]] the [[fleece]] from a [[sheep]] etc by [[clipping]]
#{{physics}} To [[deform]] because of [[shearing]] [[force]]s

